    {
      "id": "1527038479735853189",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-15T19:45:44.572+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "First draft of 0p5x1 CoB.  Revisions compared with previous CoBs / previous attempt at this one:\n- Principle of least surprise:  Schematic has pin 1 where the project template does.  Pads (except for power) are in the same order on the mezzanine connector as on the die.\n- Wafer space logo moved to bottom right, so it matches the top left position on the run 2 dies\n- Solder mask added between the die and pad ring\n- No Ground flood fill exclusion between die and pad ring\n- Pin 1 marker is in copper\n\nFeedback welcome",
      "author": {
        "id": "691780627338625077",
        "name": "rebelmike",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "RebelMike",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2026-07_media/49aaff687e56f04e7bbdedf0077bab75-7DDB4.png"
      },
      "attachments": [
        {
          "id": "1527038479383658566",
          "url": "2026-07_media/image-14C26.png",
          "fileName": "image.png",
          "fileSizeBytes": 104488
        }
      ],
      "embeds": [],
      "stickers": [],
      "reactions": [],
      "mentions": [],
      "inlineEmojis": []
    },
    {
      "id": "1527039428411785236",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-15T19:49:30.754+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "One note: It'll be natural to hold these the other way up, to match the die orientation.  I think that's good, but it does mean mezzanine connector pin 1 is at the bottom, which is potentially confusing.  (Although at least on my motherboard, and I saw on the KianV one too, the CoB is mounted upside down anyway).\nAnd one question: The ground plated through holes between the die and the pad ring, sohuld they just be normal vias?  Then all the holes should be tented, which may avoid issues with bubbles?",
      "author": {
        "id": "691780627338625077",
        "name": "rebelmike",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "RebelMike",
